---
// biome-ignore lint/correctness/noUnusedImports: Used in the Astro template below.
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Documentation - Termide"
  description="Install, configure, and use Termide features including the Command bar, settings, remote access, file tools, and dockable terminals."
>
  <div class="docs-container">
    <aside class="docs-sidebar">
      <nav class="docs-nav">
        <h3>Documentation</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="#installation">Installation</a></li>
          <li><a href="#workspace">Workspace</a></li>
          <li><a href="#command-bar">Command Bar</a></li>
          <li><a href="#settings">Settings</a></li>
          <li><a href="#remote-access">Remote Access</a></li>
          <li><a href="#files">Files</a></li>
          <li><a href="#shortcuts">Shortcuts</a></li>
          <li><a href="#development">Development</a></li>
        </ul>
      </nav>
    </aside>

    <main class="docs-content">
      <h1 class="docs-title">Termide Documentation</h1>

      <section id="installation" class="docs-section">
        <h2>Installation</h2>
        <p>
          Download a packaged build from <a href="https://github.com/markwylde/termide/releases">GitHub Releases</a>, or build from source when you want to work on the app.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>macOS Apple Silicon and Intel builds</li>
          <li>Linux AppImage builds</li>
          <li>Node.js 24+ and npm 10+ for development</li>
        </ul>
        <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/markwylde/termide.git
cd termide
npm ci
npm run dev
npm run build</code></pre>
      </section>

      <section id="workspace" class="docs-section">
        <h2>Workspace</h2>
        <p>
          Termide organizes work into project tabs. Each project can have a root folder, color, short icon, file explorer state, and its own docked terminal layout.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Create a terminal with <code>Cmd/Ctrl+T</code>.</li>
          <li>Create a project with <code>Cmd/Ctrl+P</code>.</li>
          <li>Split the active terminal horizontally or vertically from the Command bar or shortcuts.</li>
          <li>Double-click project or terminal tabs to rename them and adjust color/icon styling.</li>
          <li>Pop the active tab into another window with <code>Cmd/Ctrl+Shift+P</code>.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section id="command-bar" class="docs-section">
        <h2>Command Bar</h2>
        <p>
          The Command bar opens with <code>Cmd/Ctrl+L</code>. It searches built-in app commands and saved macros in one keyboard-first menu.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Search commands such as split terminal, clear terminal, save active tab, and set project root.</li>
          <li>Run macros directly from the same launcher.</li>
          <li>Use arrow keys to navigate and Enter to run the selected item.</li>
          <li>Customize the shortcut in Settings under Shortcuts.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section id="settings" class="docs-section">
        <h2>Settings</h2>
        <p>
          Settings are grouped by appearance, shell, cursor, interaction, keyboard, scrolling, accessibility, theme, and remote access.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Preview terminal appearance while changing font, line height, cursor, and theme values.</li>
          <li>Capture, clear, reset, and inspect shortcut conflicts.</li>
          <li>Configure shell launch behavior and working-directory handling.</li>
          <li>Manage remote access host, origin, TLS certificate, and key paths.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section id="remote-access" class="docs-section">
        <h2>Remote Access</h2>
        <p>
          Remote access lets a paired browser connect to Termide through the local HTTPS host. Start it from the remote access menu or the Remote Access settings section.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Generate a fresh pairing QR code for browser setup.</li>
          <li>Use the default local origin <code>https://localhost:9443</code>, or configure a different HTTPS origin.</li>
          <li>View paired devices, active connections, and recent audit events.</li>
          <li>Revoke devices and close live connections from Settings.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section id="files" class="docs-section">
        <h2>Files</h2>
        <p>
          The file explorer sits beside your terminal layout and uses the active project root folder.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Browse folders and open files without leaving the project.</li>
          <li>Edit text files with Monaco and save the active tab with <code>Cmd/Ctrl+S</code>.</li>
          <li>Preview markdown, images, PDFs, large files, binary data, and Git diffs.</li>
          <li>Create, rename, delete, refresh, and open terminal sessions from file and folder context menus.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section id="shortcuts" class="docs-section">
        <h2>Default Shortcuts</h2>
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Shortcut</th>
              <th>Action</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td><code>Cmd/Ctrl+L</code></td><td>Open Command bar</td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>Cmd/Ctrl+T</code></td><td>Create a new terminal tab</td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>Cmd/Ctrl+P</code></td><td>Create a new project</td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>Cmd/Ctrl+K</code></td><td>Clear terminal</td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>Cmd/Ctrl+S</code></td><td>Save active tab</td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>Cmd/Ctrl+Shift+-</code></td><td>Split horizontally</td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>Cmd/Ctrl+Shift+\</code></td><td>Split vertically</td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>Cmd/Ctrl+Shift+P</code></td><td>Pop out active tab</td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>Cmd/Ctrl+W</code></td><td>Close active tab</td></tr>
            <tr><td><code>Cmd/Ctrl+R</code></td><td>Set project root to active terminal working directory</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>

      <section id="development" class="docs-section">
        <h2>Development</h2>
        <p>
          The docs screenshots are automated through Electron Playwright. It rebuilds the app, launches Termide with isolated user data, stages a 1000x600 workspace, and writes the marketing images into the docs public folder.
        </p>
        <pre><code>npm run docs:screenshots
npm run docs:build
npm run test:e2e</code></pre>
        <p>
          The script lives at <code>scripts/generate-docs-screenshots.mjs</code>. It generates the hero workspace plus Command bar, files, settings, and remote access screenshots.
        </p>
      </section>
    </main>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .docs-container {
    max-width: 1360px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2.5rem 2rem 5rem;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 250px minmax(0, 1fr);
    gap: 3rem;
  }

  .docs-sidebar {
    position: sticky;
    top: 96px;
    height: fit-content;
  }

  .docs-nav h3 {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .docs-nav ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .docs-nav a {
    display: block;
    padding: 0.48rem 0.75rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-size: 0.94rem;
  }

  .docs-nav a:hover {
    background: var(--bg-tertiary);
    color: var(--text-primary);
    opacity: 1;
  }

  .docs-content {
    max-width: 820px;
  }

  .docs-title {
    font-size: clamp(2.4rem, 5vw, 4rem);
    line-height: 1;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .docs-section {
    margin-bottom: 3.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 3.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
  }

  .docs-section:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .docs-section h2 {
    font-size: 1.8rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .docs-section p,
  .docs-section li,
  .docs-section td {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .docs-section ul {
    margin: 1rem 0;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }

  .docs-section li {
    margin: 0.45rem 0;
  }

  .docs-section a {
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 0.16em;
  }

  .docs-section pre {
    margin: 1.4rem 0;
  }

  .docs-section table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .docs-section th,
  .docs-section td {
    padding: 0.72rem 0.85rem;
    text-align: left;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
  }

  .docs-section th {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .docs-container {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 2rem;
      padding: 1.5rem 1rem 4rem;
    }

    .docs-sidebar {
      position: relative;
      top: 0;
    }

    .docs-nav ul {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 0.4rem;
    }
  }
</style>
